### ============================================================
### MCP Test Flow — Tasks API
### Run requests top-to-bottom; each step builds on the previous.
### ============================================================

### 1. Initialize session — captures Mcp-Session-Id into {{mcp_session_id}}
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2024-11-05",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": {
      "name": "http-test-client",
      "version": "1.0"
    }
  }
}

> {%
  client.global.set("mcp_session_id", response.headers.valueOf("Mcp-Session-Id"));
%}

### 2. Acknowledge initialization (required by MCP protocol)
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "notifications/initialized",
  "params": {}
}

### 3. List available tools — verify all 5 tools are registered
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/list",
  "params": {}
}

### ============================================================
### Happy-path lifecycle: create → list → get → complete → delete
### ============================================================

### 4. Create a task
# @name createTask
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 3,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "create_task",
    "arguments": {
      "title": "Buy groceries",
      "description": "Milk, eggs, bread"
    }
  }
}

### 5. Create a second task (to make list non-trivial)
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 4,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "create_task",
    "arguments": {
      "title": "Write tests",
      "description": "Add unit tests for the tasks API"
    }
  }
}

### 6. List all tasks — should show both tasks above
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 5,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "list_tasks",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### 7. Get a specific task by ID
# Replace <task-id> with the `id` value from step 4's response
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 6,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_task",
    "arguments": {
      "task_id": "<task-id>"
    }
  }
}

### 8. Complete the task — completed should flip to true
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 7,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "complete_task",
    "arguments": {
      "task_id": "<task-id>"
    }
  }
}

### 9. Get task again — verify completed=true
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 8,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_task",
    "arguments": {
      "task_id": "<task-id>"
    }
  }
}

### 10. Delete the task
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 9,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "delete_task",
    "arguments": {
      "task_id": "<task-id>"
    }
  }
}

### ============================================================
### Error cases
### ============================================================

### 11. Get non-existent task — expect 404 from upstream API
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 10,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_task",
    "arguments": {
      "task_id": "does-not-exist"
    }
  }
}

### 12. Delete non-existent task — expect 404 from upstream API
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 11,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "delete_task",
    "arguments": {
      "task_id": "does-not-exist"
    }
  }
}

### 13. Create task without required field — expect validation error
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 12,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "create_task",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### ============================================================
### JWT forwarding check
### ============================================================

### 14. Call a tool with a Bearer token — verify it reaches upstream API
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.test
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 13,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "list_tasks",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### ============================================================
### Protocol edge cases
### ============================================================

### 15. Unknown method — expect JSON-RPC error -32601
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Mcp-Session-Id: {{mcp_session_id}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 14,
  "method": "unknown/method",
  "params": {}
}

### 16. Call without session ID — should be rejected or start a new session
POST http://localhost:8080/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 15,
  "method": "tools/list",
  "params": {}
}
